Jared and JD,
If you need to respond to CC on this issue, you can simply state the following:
1.	Shift4 is only willing to provide the customer with a "Full POS' system if they are willing to sign
an agreement that includes a 3.5 year term with a $12.95 per month customer support fee.
(The language about Shift4 being a reseller - which we are - is present)
If the customer is not willing to do so, Shift4 will not provide a "Full POS" system.
2.	Shift4 is willing to provide the customer with a "Turnkey POS' system with the Card Connect IDG
but (a) that system will provide revenue to Shift4 and (b) the customer must be willing to sign
an agreement that includes a 3.5 year term with a $12.95 per month customer support fee.
(The language about Shif4 being a reseller - which we are - is present)
If the customer is not willing to do so, Shift4 will not provide a "Turnkey POS" system.
3.	If the customer is interested in another POS option, we would be happy to work with the
customer and the Card Connect IDG to effect an integration to that system.
The bottom line is that we are not going to provide a system to any customer in which we generate no
revenue and have a significant cost - unless they are prepared to meet the requirements we have always
had for such customers - a long term contract with a monthly support fee.
And as I have said before, we have no interest in providing our "Full POS' to a customer who is not
willing to meet the same terms that all of the other customers who receive that system must meet. It
would make no sense from a business perspective.
Don
